================================================================================
ROCN NOTES
================================================================================
This is the highest-value folder for actual ROCN design because it exposes the HIP API surface.

Priority files for deeper ROCN mapping:

1. include/hip/hip_runtime_api.h
   Map to rocn.host runtime calls.

2. include/hip/hip_runtime.h
   Map to ROCN host/device bridge and future kernel launch syntax.

3. include/hip/hiprtc.h
   Map to future ROCN runtime compilation or staged kernel compilation.

4. include/hip/driver_types.h and include/hip/library_types.h
   Map HIP type vocabulary into Netiv-native type wrappers.

5. include/hip/hip_fp16.h, hip_fp8.h, hip_bfloat16.h
   Important for AI/tensor/low-precision work.

6. include/hip/math_functions.h and hip_math_constants.h
   Important for device math coverage.

7. include/hip/cooperative_groups/ and hip_cooperative_groups.h
   Important for group/thread/block collective behavior.

Do not copy these headers into NetivLang yet. This is an upstream map for original ROCN design work.
